{
  "stem": "13258.4",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We came in that camp that was near the city town of Pulawy-- P-U-L-A-W-Y-- on the Vistula, in a little village, there, outside in the forest.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "There were-- some of the barracks had been destroyed.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "There were still peeled potatoes in the kitchen, in the big, huge vats where they were supposed to be cooked.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I found, in there is a volume of interesting documents from a one policeman, who apparently had joined, then was reluctant and escaped.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And there was such a volume of paperwork with him escaping and being caught and escaping and caught.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And that was-- but that was the first time we also, I realized that the Germans had been training foreign policemen, in the war.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Other camps, I did not come by until after the war.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I passed by quite often at Auschwitz, because there was an important railroad going there, which I took to go to some villages in the mountains during vacation time, so-- but otherwise, I did not come.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "We were not too far from Stutthof, apparently.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And as I-- at one point, the first Jews after the war who had survived were a group of Jewish youngsters.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "I mean, youngsters-- they were in their late teens, beginning twenties probably-- who had survived.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I believe, it was Stutthof.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I met, later on, quite a few of them in Katowice and Sosnowiec-- in [INAUDIBLE] and Sosnowiec.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "They were in [? kibbutz, ?] kind of, preparing to go to Israel.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And I spent the high holidays in 1945 in [INAUDIBLE] at a kibbutz, after a lot of haggling with my military commander, who wouldn't give me off a day.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were taken, first of all, in Tarnopol, to the jail, and it was a terrible-- There was, like, an old fortress.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
